Job Description:
About us
Evadata’s mission is to transform the insurance industry through data. We are targeting the life and annuity market, which dates back to the sixteenth century, and has often lagged behind in the era of information technology. We believe the future of the life and annuity market is in unlocking and uniting massive troves of data. We’re building the first-ever platform to help primary carriers improve every step of the customer journey and fast-forward the industry as a whole into a better future.
Data Analyst – Insights Team
Evadata is an ambitious new venture – backed by leading life and annuity carriers in the United States. Evadata’s purpose is to develop solutions so that carriers can better serve policyholders. All activities are pursued in strict compliance with all data privacy and data security regulations and protocols.
Evadata Insights houses our data-driven products by which we strive to help our clients get timely answers to strategic business questions and keep a pulse on emerging trends in the market.
Evadata is comprised of a fast-growing team of industry veterans and technologists who are passionate about problem solving, innovation, and helping end-consumers.
About The Opportunity
Evadata Insights is seeking a Data Analyst who will evaluate emerging data sources, process data for databases and studies, and collaborate on new products and services.
As a data analyst, you will evaluate alternative data sources for life insurance, identify trends for customers, process data for different products and studies, and create summary reports and documentation for clients. This role is critical to the organization and a key partner to our data science team.
Specifically, you will:
Participate in the development and evolution of data-driven software products and solutions;
Collaborate on the development of a data strategy framework;
Work with internal teams to analyze and interpret life insurance data using
Excel;
Coordinate with clients to manage data requests and submissions;
Clean and process raw data for analytics;
Create summary reports for clients;
Research emerging data vendors and relay findings;
Follow changes in regulations related to life insurance use cases for healthcare data;
Monitor pertinent information concerning mortality reporting and related statistics, such as changes in the CDC's guidelines and the SOA's life tables.
About You
Awareness of the life insurance market. Experience in the insurance industry
(and/or clinical data) preferred;
Advanced Excel skills for data cleansing and normalizing data. Bonus if you have programming skills in Python or R;
Extremely detail oriented, naturally curious, investigative individual with dynamic problem-solving abilities;
Strong verbal and written communication with a customer orientation focus;
Willingness to immerse yourself in ambiguous projects and work through ill- defined concepts;
Enjoy working in a fast-paced work environment and on multiple tasks;
Team player with ability to build relationships and drive consensus;
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience;
2-5 years of experience in roles with hands on quantitative analysis.
Company Benefits
Fast-paced, collaborative startup culture with colleagues who like to learn by doing and are excited about playing a part in industry transformation at large.
Remote friendly organization with a distributed team across eastern, central, and mountain time zones. Work from where you want to work.
Diversity and Inclusion
We’re committed to building opportunities for underrepresented groups and creating a diverse and inclusive culture from the ground up.
